jquery.querystring.js is an easy querystring-parser plugin for jquery, 
it provides mechanism parse querystring and hash.

### USE JQUERY.QUERYSTRING.JS ##########################
Use jquery.querystring.js is simple.

Step 1:
	Add reference in you HTML file.
		jquery:
		<script src="http://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.6.4.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
		
		jquery.querystring:
		<script src="jquery.querystring-0.1.min.js" type="text/javascript"></script>
		
Step 2:
	Just use it.
		$.querystring('a'); // Get the value of the parameter 'a' <you page>?a=10
		$.hash('c'); // Get the value of the parameter 'a' <you page>#a=10
		

### RELEASE HISTORY ##########################
V 0.1	-->	First release, 
			$.querystring('<parameter>'); 
			$.hash('<parameter>');


